1
2 (a) For purposes of this section:
3
4 (i) "Autologous blood donation" means when a
5 person donates the person's own blood for personal use
6 during a future medical procedure;
7
8 (ii) "Direct blood donation" means when a person
9 donates the person's blood specifically for the use of
10 another person during the other person's future medical
11 procedure.
12
13 (b) A hospital or other health care facility licensed
14 under this title shall allow a person on whom a medical
15 procedure is to be performed at the facility to donate a
16 health care provider-ordered autologous or direct blood
17 donation before the medical procedure if the facility
18 performs blood donations.
19
20 (c) A blood bank that facilitates autologous or
21 direct blood donations shall comply with a health care
22 provider's order prescribing an autologous or direct blood
23 donation for a person, unless the person donating blood is
2 HB0135

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0375
1 in ill health, has a heart condition that makes donating
2 blood inadvisable, the person weighs too little to donate
3 blood, or the person cannot or should not donate blood for
4 any other reason.
5
6 (d) A blood bank may charge not more than their
7 regular fee to facilitate an autologous or direct blood
8 donation ordered by a health care provider under subsection
9 (c) of this section. The blood bank may charge a fee to
10 store the donated blood until it is used by the person
11 meant to receive it.
12
13 Section 2. The department of health shall promulgate
14 all rules necessary to implement this act.
